Package: dipca
Type: Package
Title: Dynamic Inner Principal Component Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(
    given = c("Bradley", "R."),
    family = "Buchsbaum",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    email = "brad.buchsbaum@gmail.com")
Description: Methods for dynamic inner principal component analysis (DiPCA),
    dynamic inner canonical correlation analysis (DiCCA), and dynamic inner
    partial least squares (DiPLS) for multivariate time series. These methods
    extract latent components that follow autoregressive models, enabling
    temporal prediction and reconstruction. Based on Dong and Qin (2018)
    <doi:10.1016/j.jprocont.2017.05.002>, Dong and Qin (2018)
    <doi:10.1016/j.ifacol.2018.09.379>, and Dong and Qin (2018)
    <doi:10.1016/j.jprocont.2018.04.006>. Integrates with the 'multivarious'
    package for consistent preprocessing and projection interfaces.
